# UI guardrails

Apply this rule whenever working on pages, components, layout, styling, theming, or visual refactors.

## Do not break foundation

- Do not overwrite `src/index.css` with a minimal reset unless explicitly asked.
- Do not remove Tailwind imports, shadcn-related styles, theme variables, or animation utilities without confirmation.
- Do not remove `tw-animate-css`, `utils.ts`, or alias-based imports unless confirmed unused and safe.
- Do not delete starter files as a side effect of a UI task unless the task explicitly requests cleanup.

## Preferred workflow

- Make additive changes first.
- Preserve working foundation and layer new UI on top.
- Modify only the files needed for the requested screen or feature.
- Keep diffs small and reviewable.
- When possible, complete one screen/feature at a time.

## Implementation style

- Build production-looking UI, not placeholder toy layouts.
- Prefer clean spacing, strong hierarchy, restrained color usage, and good dark-mode defaults.
- Use shadcn/ui primitives for dialogs, sheets, dropdowns, popovers, tabs, buttons, inputs, tables, cards, badges, and forms.
- Keep components composable and split large screens into smaller sections.

## When asked to simplify

If the user asks to “simplify” something:
- simplify the feature implementation, not the project foundation;
- keep Tailwind + shadcn/ui setup intact;
- avoid touching global config unless necessary.

## Before completion

- Show the diff through the normal workflow.
- Summarize which files were changed.
- Mention if any global CSS or config file was edited and why.
